metadata.name: RULES (for Elementary Cellular Automata) #268
metadata.description:
An important element of generative art is emergence. The most famous algorithm for this is probably Cellular Automata (CA).

However, numerous generative artists have created works using CA, which has lost its visual freshness and is like chewing gum that has lost its taste.

Although it is such a classic algorithm, adding my own little ideas to it and finding a new "flavor" is the reason why I code.

Here, the subject is 1D Elementary Cellular Automata, the simplest of all cellular automata. 1D Elementary Cellular Automata has 256 different rules, which change the shapes produced. This work aims to create more complex shapes by randomly selecting some of those rules and placing multiple of them on the screen.

The on/off of the CA cell is often likened to the behavior of living creatures.As of 2022, in the country where I live, prices are rising, wages are not increasing, and COVID-19 has not yet ended. I created this work with the image of people at the mercy of these various rules.

---

Screen click: Change rules
S key: Save png
L key: Show/hide grid

metadata.name: Life has no scores #100
metadata.description:
We cannot compose life, at best we hum along to the melodies that life has been played in front of us. Looking back at the scores of our lives, the notations are never neatly noted, but fully felt.  Rewinding the songs of life are our memories, whether sad, happy, angry, or melancholy. It is not clear whether I am dreaming or awake, but our songs all do end. 

In this final drop (for ?), I have reused the first ever class calligraphy(){} I have written from my genesis drop “Nothing comes from nothing”. As time passes, 10 drops later, across almost to the year, I am grateful for the progress I have made, as an artist, and more importantly as a human. After all, what is behind the code of generative art is a human being. 

Scores of music, scrolls of calligraphy, calendar or diary, notating life, time passes, and changes are inevitable. Sometimes we sing louder in laughter and joy, sometimes we scribble in uneasiness, sometimes we just get lost in neon lights. Life goes on. You and me, all the same and yet different.  

There are too many friend artists, friend collectors, fxhash team members, to thank for helping me through this journey. I would like to pay homage to Rudxane in this work, who has taken me under his wings, mentoring and encouraging me in art as well as showing me some degen stuff on the side:-). This homage is not copy-minting, or copying of styles, which I do not have the coding skills to do so even if I wanted to. But it is the influence of taste in many works of Rudxane. In a vague but agreeable taste, I present to you Life has no scores. 

What I was taught was disrupted, and grid studies left unfinished, and oh do we have a BINGO?

Tested on Chrome. Other browsers may render different or not at all (firefox)

Press ‘2’ to save png.

metadata.name: Manu #141
metadata.description:
Manu
---------------

A collector-led exploration of minimalist imperfect line work.

Outputs are generated from a combination of the minter's address, their choice from one of 50 seeds, and options to adjust how the generated surface is presented.

Palettes are named after native New Zealand birds and range from the subdued to the colorful.

There are no especially rare traits so mint what you love :)

---------------

Controls:
S - Export as png
H - Toggle high resolution

metadata.name: Infinite Rhythmic Universe - PROTOTYPE #35
metadata.description:
This is a prototype that generates rhythm patterns for samplers and FM synthesized sounds in web audio. Various shapes are generated reactively according to the tone according to the sound.

There are some audio post-processes available as parameters, and they are also working as visual post-processes at the same time.

using: 
* Audio for RNBO.js
* Three.js for Visuals

metadata.name: Gravures #169
metadata.description:
Gravures are digital paintings inspired by many influences. They recreating abstract nature using horizontal lines and a touch of randomness, resulting in a natural and organic appearance.

------------

In live mode :  
 - Press ’s’ to save a png - A4 (21 x 29.7cm) is the default size 
- Add an url parameter to choose between physical sizes (cm) : 20x30, 30x40, a4 or a3. 
At the end of the url you can add « &size=20x30 », « &size=a3 » …

metadata.name: Echo #56
metadata.description:
"Echo" is a generative abstract artwork made with p5js and custom shaders

Based on my previous experience, known patterns and existing style preferences
Artwork is 100% code, no images used.

CONTROLS
KEYS:

- 1-3: Set resolution from 1x to 3x of the current dimension (possibly slower performance in higher values)
- S: Save a png file with the current resolution

metadata.name: Eikonal identities #64
metadata.description:
Works in the invisible
Inevitable shadows
Digital exorcism
Silicon catharsis


Eikonal
- Usually "eikonal equation" : the wave-like description of the propagation of light through a medium
- In optics, relative to the formation of an image
- anagram : e-kaolin



-----
* What/How *

Product of the code.

A picture generated by a succession of chaotic events applied to a system of 4.2 million particles.
The drawing process consists of mixing and projecting the particles randomly in space.

Each image is unique and depends only on the address of minter's wallet and current iteration number.

-----
* Technics *

- Hand written code in Javascript, GLSL
- Uses three.js library, WebGL particles, physics
- Generates a FullHD PNG (1080x1080 px bitmap 24bits)
- Takes less than 15 seconds of generation on a relatively recent GPU (>2017)

-----
@HAL09999 – August 8th, 2023
https://twitter.com/HAL09999
https://instagram.com/hal09999
https://danslesnuages.xyz

metadata.name: Pintura Perpétua #47
metadata.description:
I designed this livecode with the intention of creating a perpetual art machine, the colors become more solid according to the distance of the pendulum from the canvas, the perpetual movement of the pendulums and their brushes create a colorful dance, bringing different textures in its movement. its possibilities between angles and colors create infinite possibilitys of movement. the trace of luma, the rotation of angle and position of the shapes creates stochastic abstract painting.

made in hydra
Marcelo Moura - 2022 - CC0
